 per year, Treasury bonds a little over 5%, and Treasury bills less
 than 4%. Don't expect your <a href="http://www.getrichslowly.org/blog/2009/05/21/no-crystal-ball-required-getting-better-investment-returns-without-guessing/">investments</a>
 to do significantly better over the long haul.</i>
